To prepare an emulator:

1. gcc mkmk.c -o mkmk

   This produces an executable, mkmk, which can be used to create
   a makefile.

2. For machine <target> (e.g. linux maci386 macosx solaris, sgi) execute

   do-<target> <additional arguments> (e.g. do-linux spi)

   This calls mkmk with <additional arguments> to create a makefile for
   <target>.

3. make



